# ============================================
# Firebase Configuration - Environment Variables
# ============================================
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
#
# 1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com/
# 2. Create a new Firebase project or use an existing one
# 3. Enable Firestore Database in your Firebase console:
#    - Click "Firestore Database" in the left menu
#    - Click "Create database"
#    - Start in "Test mode" for development (opens read/write)
#    - Choose a Cloud Firestore location (e.g., us-central1)
#
# 4. Get your Firebase config:
#    - Go to Project Settings (gear icon) > General
#    - Scroll down to "Your apps"
#    - Click "Add app" and select "Web" (</>)
#    - Register your app with a nickname
#    - Copy the configuration values below
#
# 5. Deploy Firestore security rules:
#    - Install Firebase CLI: npm install -g firebase-tools
#    - Login: firebase login
#    - Init: firebase init firestore
#    - Deploy: firebase deploy --only firestore:rules
#
# 6. For Vercel deployment:
#    - Go to your Vercel project dashboard
#    - Click "Settings" > "Environment Variables"
#    - Add each variable below with the "Plain Text" type
#    - Redeploy your project after adding variables
#
# ============================================

# Firebase API Key
# Find this in Firebase Console > Project Settings > General > Web API Key
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=AIzaSyXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# Firebase Auth Domain
# Format: your-project-id.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project-id.firebaseapp.com

# Firebase Project ID
# Find this in Firebase Console > Project Settings > General > Project ID
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id

# Firebase Storage Bucket
# Format: your-project-id.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project-id.appspot.com

# Firebase Messaging Sender ID
# Find this in Firebase Console > Project Settings > Cloud Messaging > Sender ID
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=123456789012

# Firebase App ID
# Find this in Firebase Console > Project Settings > General > App ID
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=1:123456789012:web:abcdef1234567890abcdef

# ============================================
# NOTES:
# ============================================
#
# - These variables are prefixed with VITE_ for client-side access
# - In Vercel, create environment variables without quotes
# - Make sure to add these to your Vercel project settings
# - DO NOT commit actual values to version control
# - Keep this .env.example file for reference only
# - Create a .env.local file for local development (not tracked in git)
#
# ============================================
